> > 
> > What's the issue with the _hoth override?
> 
> Hmm, there were some discussion downstream on how we should be upstreaming hoth related things, as we will have to change a few things regarding what our tooling expects, etc.
> 
> Maybe in this case, it's ok

My only concern with upstreaming overrides is proliferating overrides that don't make sense outside of google. The hoth override is something we will need, since we have quite a few places that have different behavior when it is used. My only concern with the hoth stuff is that we are not only upstreaming but also renaming a fairly large amount of functionality, so we need to be careful not to subtly break our systems in the process. The other patches so far have been more isolated and verifiably correct.
